def analyzeData(path, normalize = False):
  dataGenerator = preprocessing.image.ImageDataGenerator(
      rescale = ((1.0/255.0) if normalize else None)
  )
  data = dataGenerator.flow_from_directory(
      path,
      target_size = (80,80),
      batch_size = 32,
      color_mode = "grayscale"
  )
  print("Size of data is: %d - Number of classes is : %d - Classes are : %s" % (data.n, data.num_classes, data.class_indices))
  return data

def getLabel(onehotLabel):
    return np.argmax(onehotLabel)
In [ ]:
def getDataFromEachClass(data):
    res = {}
    image = data[0]
    onehotLabel = data[1]
    for i in range(len(image)):
        if getLabel(onehotLabel[i]) not in res:
            res[getLabel(onehotLabel[i])] = image[i].reshape(80,80)
    return res
In [ ]:
def showImage(img,label):
    plt.imshow(img, cmap="gray")
    plt.title("%s" % label)
In [ ]:
def plot(indata):
    labels = {0: 'COVID19', 1: 'NORMAL', 2: 'PNEUMONIA'}
    data = getDataFromEachClass(indata)
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
    for i in range(len(data)):
        plt.subplot(1,3,i+1)
        showImage(data[i],labels[i])

def countEachClass(data):
    res = {}
    labels = {0: 'COVID19', 1: 'NORMAL', 2: 'PNEUMONIA'}
    for i in range(data.n):
        label = data.labels[i]
        strLabel = labels[label]
        if strLabel in res:
            res[strLabel] += 1
        else:
            res[strLabel] = 1
    return res
In [ ]:
def distributionPlot(inDict):
    plt.bar(range(len(inDict)), list(inDict.values()))
    plt.xticks(range(len(inDict)), list(inDict.keys()))
    plt.show()

def addInputLayer():
    input = layers.Input(shape=(80, 80, 1))
    return input
In [ ]:
def addHiddenLayer(preLayer, units, actFunc):
    layer = layers.Dense(units, activation=actFunc)(preLayer)
    return layer
In [ ]:
def addOutputLayer(preLayer, labelCnt, actFunc):
    outLayer = layers.Dense(labelCnt, activation=actFunc)(preLayer)
    return outLayer
In [ ]:
def createNetwork(inputLayer, outputLayer, opt, lossFunc):
    model = models.Model(inputs = inputLayer, outputs = outputLayer)
    model.compile(optimizer = opt, loss = lossFunc, metrics=['accuracy'])
    return model
In [6]:
def plotHistoryInfo(history, epochNum):
    toPlotTrainAcc = history["accuracy"]
    toPlotTestAcc = history["val_accuracy"]
    toPlotTrainLoss = history["loss"]
    toPlotTestLoss = history["val_loss"]
    epochNum = list(range(1,len(toPlotTestAcc)+1))
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,5))
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(epochNum, toPlotTrainAcc)
    plt.plot(epochNum, toPlotTestAcc)
    plt.legend(["train","test"])
    plt.title("Accuracy",fontweight = "bold")
    plt.xlabel("Epoch count")
    plt.ylabel("Accuracy")
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(epochNum, toPlotTrainLoss)
    plt.plot(epochNum,toPlotTestLoss)
    plt.legend(["train","test"])
    plt.title("Loss",fontweight = "bold")
    plt.xlabel("Epoch count")
    plt.ylabel("Loss")
    plt.show()

def getLabelBatchByBatch(data):
    labels = []
    batchCnt = data.n//data.batch_size if (data.n//data.batch_size == data.n/data.batch_size) else (data.n//data.batch_size) + 1
    # print(data.n, data.batch_size, batchCnt)
    for i in range(batchCnt):
        newData = data.next()
        for y in newData[1]:
      # labels.append(getLabel(y))
      # labels.append(backend.argmax(y))
            labels.append(getLabel(y))
    # print(np.array(labels))
    return np.array(labels)
In [8]:
def getReport(trainedModel, data):
    y_true = getLabelBatchByBatch(data)
    predicted = trainedModel.predict(data)
    y_pred = []
    for onehot in predicted:
        y_pred.append(getLabel(onehot))
  # y_pred = np.argmax(predicted,axis=1)
  # print("B:",y_pred)
    print(classification_report(y_true, y_pred))

input = layers.Input(shape=(80, 80, 1))
inLayer = layers.Flatten()(input)
hiddenLayer1 = layers.Dense(2048, activation="relu")(inLayer)
dropLayer1 = layers.Dropout(0.1)(hiddenLayer1)
hiddenLayer2 = layers.Dense(4096, activation="relu", kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.0001))(dropLayer1)
dropLayer2 = layers.Dropout(0.1)(hiddenLayer2)
hiddenLayer3 = layers.Dense(2024, activation="relu", kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.0001))(dropLayer2)
dropLayer3 = layers.Dropout(0.1)(hiddenLayer3)
hiddenLayer4 = layers.Dense(2048, activation="relu", kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.0001))(dropLayer3)
dropLayer4 = layers.Dropout(0.1)(hiddenLayer4)
outLayer = layers.Dense(3, activation="softmax", kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.0001))(dropLayer4)
